article.headline: Florida International 70, Kennesaw St. 68
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Alex Galindo hit a layup with 1:23 remaining and Elvis Lora added two free throws in the final 30 seconds to give Florida International a 70-68 victory over Kennesaw State on Saturday. Kennesaw (1-4) had taken a 66-65 lead with 1:37 left on a three-point play by Andre Morgan before Galindo put FIU (3-3) ahead to stay. The Owls had chances to take the lead, but Ronell Wooten and Golden Ingle failed on shots. Shuan Stegall missed the front end of a one-and-one free throw with :01 left, giving the victory to the Golden Panthers. The game had 18 lead changes and it was tied 14 times. Johwen Villegas led FIU with 23 points and Galindo added 14. Stegall paced Kennesaw with 19, Wooten had 18 and Ingle 16.
